<p>North Korea launched multiple short-range ballistic missiles on Wednesday, with South Korea&#x27;s military saying several projectiles were fired from an area south of Pyongyang toward the east sea on October 22, 2025 [aljazeera.com#1][france24.com#1][firstpost.com#1]. The launches — described by Seoul as the country&#x27;s first ballistic tests in months — came a week before the Asia‑Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) leaders&#x27; meeting in South Korea and days before U.S. President Trump’s scheduled visit, raising regional security concerns [euronews.com#1][dawn.com#1][newarab.com#1]. South Korea and Japan have increased monitoring and information-sharing after the launches; Pyongyang had not issued an immediate public comment in initial reports [rt.com#1][aljazeera.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/Pt8KLJ-W2UCQ17tbc20lqfUu0GBt8BzHFQOF5C5-RVqqstfvyJTanXLj6Wjbxn7DedoNP1e0HL4FznOGTv56-NrEWX5jGtFY7iDpIrrEnd85' alt='People watch a TV broadcasting a news report on North Korea firing a short-range ballistic missile towards the sea off its east coast, at a railway station in Seoul, South Korea, on Oct 22, 2025.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Timing and novelty: Seoul said this was Pyongyang&#x27;s first ballistic missile firing since May, and the first since President Lee Jae‑myung took office in June 2025, marking a break in months-long inactivity [dawn.com#1][dw.com#1]</li><li>Possible signalling: Analysts and commentators linked the tests to messaging ahead of APEC and U.S. President Trump&#x27;s planned visit, with some saying the launches could be intended to assert North Korea&#x27;s presence during a high-profile summit week [scmp.com#1][rt.com#1]</li><li>Recent weapons developments: Separately, Pyongyang has showcased a new alleged ICBM and completed multiple tests of a solid-fuel engine in September, steps experts say could enable quicker launch readiness for longer-range systems [newarab.com#1][scmp.com#1]</li><li>Regional monitoring: Japan&#x27;s new prime minister said Tokyo was sharing real-time tracking and warning data with the United States and South Korea following the launches [rt.com#1]</li></ul><blockquote>A response to Trump and his recent moves - Park Won‑gon</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Seoul joint chiefs of staff: The military detected several projectiles believed to be short‑range ballistic missiles launched from an area south of Pyongyang toward the east sea. (<a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/north-korea-launches-multiple-ballistic-missiles-breaking-months-long-silence-13944024.html'>Firstpost</a>)</li><li>Park Won‑gon (academic): The launch was &#x27;a response to Trump and his recent moves,&#x27; suggesting a political signal ahead of the summit. (<a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/north-korea-fires-multiple-ballistic-missiles-first-months'>New Arab</a>)</li><li>Japan (prime minister): Tokyo is sharing real‑time tracking and warning data with the United States and South Korea following the launches. (<a href='https://www.rt.com/news/626789-north-korea-ballistic-missiles/'>RT</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/22/north-korea-fires-unidentified-ballistic-missiles-towards-east-sea-seoul'>North Korea test-fires multiple ballistic missiles as APEC summit nears</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='http://www.euronews.com/2025/10/22/north-korea-has-fired-ballistic-missiles-toward-the-east-seoul-says'>North Korea resumes missile tests days before Trump&#x27;s visit to South Korea</a> - euronews.com</li><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/asia-pacific/20251022-north-korea-ballistic-missiles'>North Korea fires ballistic missiles ahead of Trump&#x27;s South Korea summit visit</a> - france24.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/north-korea-fires-ballistic-missiles-says-seoul/a-74450147'>North Korea fires ballistic missiles, says Seoul</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/week-asia/politics/ar